        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(diagnostics): prune non-idle ghost entries after failed stuck-session recovery",
        "body": "## Real behavior proof\n\n**Real environment tested**: macOS 26.6, Node v22.22.0, OpenClaw 2026.6.7 source checkout\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n```\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/logging/diagnostic.test.ts\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix**: All 71 tests pass, including the 2 new tests:\n- `prunes non-idle ghost entries that have been inactive past the extended TTL`\n- `preserves active non-idle entries whose lastActivity is within the extended TTL`\n\n```\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\n     Tests  71 passed (71)\n```\n\n**Drift proof**:\n```\n# Before (stash src/):\ngit stash push -- src/logging/diagnostic-session-state.ts\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/logging/diagnostic.test.ts\n→ 69 tests pass (2 new tests fail — expected, fix not applied)\n\n# After (stash pop):\ngit stash pop\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/logging/diagnostic.test.ts\n→ 71 tests pass ✅\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix**: Non-idle ghost entries whose lastActivity is older than 3×SESSION_STATE_TTL_MS are now pruned along with idle entries, preventing unbounded accumulation of failed-recovery entries.\n\n**What was not tested**: Live gateway restart with pre-existing ghost entries; the 3×TTL window (90 min) is too long for a practical end-to-end test. Vitest coverage is comprehensive for the prune logic itself.\n",
